Program: Discovery
Title: Theory of evolution
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxkx
Last Broadcast Date: 12 January 2000
A report on the debate of Darwin's Theory Of Evolution. Some biologists are questioning whether competition between organisms can entirely explain Darwin's findings. The big question remains - why did it take so long for life to appear on land? The explanation appears to be at odds with the idea of life as a battle. Show less